 to help them feel comfortable in the water, and enjoy it safely. DAYS/TIME:  MON - THU  5:30pm-6:00pm LEVEL 1: INTRODUCTION TO WATER SKILLS Helps children 6 and older who have little to no experience in and around the water. The objective of Level 1 is to give students success with fundamental skills and increase their comfort level around water in a safe environment. They will work on basic swimming skills and water adjustment as well as comfort. DAYS/TIME:  MON - THU   5:30pm-6:00pm LEVEL 2: FUNDAMENTAL AQUATIC SKILLS The goal of Level 2 is to successfully build on the fundamental skills from Level 1. Participants will be working towards basic stroke competence.--Pre-requisites: Children must be able to demonstrate the skills required to complete Level 1. They must be able to float independently with a basic kick. DAYS/TIME:  MON - THU   6:10pm-6:40pm LEVEL 3: STROKE DEVELOPMENT Level 3 builds on the skills learned in Level 2 while expanding knowledge and safety.--Pre-requisites: Children must be able to demonstrate the skills required to complete Level 2. They must be able to do a recognizable stroke with basic breathing technique. DAYS/TIME:  MON - THU   6:50pm-7:30pm All Levels DATES Session 1  |  June 5 - June 15  |  Register by June 2 Session 2  |  June 19 - June 29  |  Register by June 16 Session 3  |  July 10 - July 20  |  Register by July 7 Session 4  |  July 24 - August 3  |  Register by July 21 COST $45 - Students, Members, and Non-members* * Non-members must be UNT Faculty, Staff, or Retirees. Community may only register for the Lifeguarding Course and Lifeguarding and CPR Recertification Course. Classes may be combined or cancelled due to low enrollment.                             Visit Us  Pohl Recreation Center        1900 Chestnut Drive Denton, Texas 76203         Mail Us   1900 Chestnut Drive Denton, Texas 76203       Contact Us   940-565-2275 recsports@unt.edu Technical issues?                 Site last updated on May 05, 2017  Disclaimer| AA/